## 📌 What is CivicConnect?

CivicConnect is a full-stack **MERN** application where registered citizens can report local civic problems — potholes, broken streetlights, overflowing drains — and rally community support through upvoting.

The more upvotes an issue collects, the higher its priority climbs **automatically**. If the responsible authority doesn't act within a configurable time window, the issue **auto-escalates** up a 3-tier admin hierarchy (Ward → District → City), so no complaint ever gets buried.

### Why it's different from a standard complaint form

| Traditional Systems | CivicConnect |
|---------------------|-------------|
| Submit and wait forever | Real-time status tracking |
| No community input | Upvote system surfaces urgent issues |
| Single point of failure | 3-tier authority chain with auto-escalation |
| Anonymous, unverified reports | Verified citizen accounts |
| No accountability | Full public audit trail |

---

## ✨ Features

### 👤 For Citizens

- 🔐 **Verified registration** — ward/district stored at signup to route reports to the right authority automatically
- 📍 **Rich issue reports** — title, description, 15 categories, text address, interactive map pin, photo/video uploads
- 👍 **Community upvoting** — upvote issues you care about (cannot upvote your own)
- 📊 **Automatic priority upgrade via upvotes**

  | Upvotes | Priority |
  |---------|----------|
  | 0–9 | 🔵 Low |
  | 10–24 | 🟡 Medium |
  | 25–49 | 🔴 High |
  | 50+ | 🟣 Critical |

- 📈 **Live progress bar** on every issue card showing votes needed for the next priority level
- 🔺 **Escalation trail** — full history of when and why an issue moved up the chain
- 🗺️ **Interactive map** — all issues pinned with colour-coded status markers
- 🔥 **Sort modes** — Hot (by upvotes) · New (by date) · Critical (by priority)
- 🔍 **Filter panel** — by category, status, and priority simultaneously

### 🛡️ For Admins — 3-Tier Hierarchy

| Level | Role | Jurisdiction | Extra Privileges |
|-------|------|-------------|-----------------|
| **L1** | Ward Admin | Issues in their ward | — |
| **L2** | District Admin | L1 + L2 issues | Promote users to L1, delete issues |
| **L3** | City Admin | All issues | Promote anyone, full control |

- 🎚️ **Scoped dashboard** — each admin only sees issues within their jurisdiction
- ✅ **Status management** — Pending → In Progress → Resolved → Escalated
- 🔧 **Issue assignment** — assign to a specific admin at the correct level
- 🔺 **Manual escalation** — push an issue up with a written reason
- ⏱️ **Automatic idle escalation** — cron runs every 60 min; issues that exceed their idle threshold escalate automatically
- 💬 **Internal comments** — admins add updates that are visible to citizens
- 👥 **Team management** — promote/demote users directly from the admin dashboard
- 📊 **Live stats strip** — Total / Pending / In Progress / Escalated / Resolved / Critical

### 🏷️ 15 Issue Categories

| | | |
|---|---|---|
| 🗑️ Garbage & Sanitation | 💡 Street Lighting | 🛣️ Roads & Potholes |
| 💧 Water Supply | 🚰 Sewage & Drainage | 🌳 Parks & Public Spaces |
| 🔊 Noise Pollution | 🌫️ Air Pollution | 🐕 Stray Animals |
| 🏗️ Illegal Construction | ⚡ Electricity | 🚌 Public Transport |
| 🚦 Traffic & Signals | 🌿 Trees & Encroachment | 📌 Other |

