## ⚡ Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- [Node.js 18+](https://nodejs.org)
- A free [MongoDB Atlas](https://cloud.mongodb.com) account

### Step 1 — Clone the repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/civicconnect.git
cd civicconnect
```

### Step 2 — Set up the backend

```bash
cd Backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env
```

Open `Backend/.env` and fill in **two values**:

```env
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@<cluster>.mongodb.net/civicconnect?retryWrites=true&w=majority
JWT_SECRET=any_random_string_at_least_32_characters_long
```

```bash
npm run dev
```

You should see:

```
Server running on http://localhost:5000 🚀
MongoDB Connected: yourcluster.mongodb.net ✅
[Escalation] Cron started — checking every 60 min
```

### Step 3 — Set up the frontend

```bash
cd ../Frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open **http://localhost:5173**

> ✅ **No URL changes needed.** The Vite proxy in `vite.config.js` forwards all `/api/*`
> requests to the backend automatically — works on any machine without editing any file.

### Step 4 — Create your first City Admin

1. Sign up at `http://localhost:5173/signup`
2. Open **MongoDB Atlas** → Browse Collections → `users` collection
3. Find your document → click the pencil icon → update these fields:

```json
{
  "role": "admin",
  "adminLevel": 3,
  "city": "Your City Name"
}
```

4. Save → log out of the app → log back in
5. You now have **City Admin (L3)** access and can promote others from the Admin dashboard

