## 🗺️ API Reference

### Auth — `/api/auth`

| Method | Endpoint | Auth Required | Description |
|--------|----------|--------------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/register` | None | Create citizen account |
| `POST` | `/login` | None | Returns JWT token + user object |
| `GET` | `/me` | 🔒 Any user | Get current user profile |
| `PATCH` | `/promote` | 🔑 L2+ Admin | Promote a user to admin (body: `userId`, `adminLevel`, `ward`, `district`, `city`) |
| `PATCH` | `/demote` | 🔑 L2+ Admin | Demote admin to citizen (body: `userId`) |
| `GET` | `/admins` | 🔑 L1+ Admin | List all admins |

### Issues — `/api/issues`

| Method | Endpoint | Auth Required | Description |
|--------|----------|--------------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/` | None | All issues with filters + pagination |
| `GET` | `/:id` | None | Single issue with full details |
| `POST` | `/` | 🔒 Any user | Create a new issue |
| `PATCH` | `/:id/status` | 🔑 L1+ Admin | Update status + optional comment |
| `PATCH` | `/:id/assign` | 🔑 L1+ Admin | Assign to an admin |
| `PATCH` | `/:id/priority` | 🔑 L1+ Admin | Manually override priority |
| `POST` | `/:id/escalate` | 🔑 L1+ Admin | Manually escalate with reason |
| `POST` | `/:id/upvote` | 🔒 Any user | Toggle upvote (auto-upgrades priority at thresholds) |
| `POST` | `/:id/comment` | 🔒 Any user | Add a comment |
| `DELETE` | `/:id` | 🔑 L2+ Admin | Delete a single issue |
| `DELETE` | `/` | 🔑 L2+ Admin | Delete all issues |

**Query params for `GET /api/issues`:**

```
?category=Roads & Potholes
&status=Pending
&priority=High
&level=1
&page=1
&limit=20
```

---

## 🔺 How Auto-Escalation Works

```
Issue created
  └─ currentLevel : 1  (Ward Admin responsible)
  └─ priority     : Low
  └─ status       : Pending

Citizens upvote:
  10+ votes  →  priority: Medium  (idle timer: 48h × 1.0  = 48h)
  25+ votes  →  priority: High    (idle timer: 48h × 0.75 = 36h)
  50+ votes  →  priority: Critical (idle timer: 48h × 0.5 = 24h)

  When a priority threshold is crossed:
  - Priority field updates automatically
  - A system comment is added to the issue
  - lastActivityAt resets (fresh idle timer)

Escalation cron (every 60 min checks all unresolved issues):
  L1 idle > threshold  →  currentLevel: 2, status: Escalated, assignedTo: cleared
  L2 idle > threshold  →  currentLevel: 3, status: Escalated, assignedTo: cleared
  L3                   →  no further escalation — City Admin must act
```

All thresholds are configurable via environment variables — no code changes needed.

